            <creation>This story, with the short title "Gabra Maryam Helps a Young Man," is recent: the earliest PEMM manuscript* in which this story appears is from around<date>1875</date>.Originally composed in <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName></creation>
            <abstract>
                <p>A man who desired the heavenly kingdom decided to become a monk and serve as Gabra Maryam’s disciple. But by the time he reached Dabra Alegwien, Gabra Maryam had died. Though saddened, the man still became a monk at that monastery. Sometime later, this same man was spirited away to the cathedral at Aksum. There, Gabra Maryam appeared to him in a luminous robe and led him to the veranda, where Mary stood blessing the clergy. The man watched as angels crowned Gabra Maryam. Then the angels placed a headband on the monk’s head and marched him outside the church before returning him to Alegwien.</p>
            </abstract>
